definitions.definition: Preceding all others of a series or kind; the ordinal of one; earliest .
examples: The first day of September 2013 was a Sunday.
I was the first runner to reach the finish line, and won the race.

definitions.definition: Most eminent or exalted; most excellent; chief; highest.
examples: Demosthenes was the first orator of Greece.

definitions.definition: Of or belonging to a first family .
Coming right after the zeroth in things that use zero-based numbering .
